message.content:
1. An economic evaluation was conducted comparing Hickman arm and TIVAS arm.
2. The Hickman arm was associated with a greater mean cost per patient.
3. The mean cost per patient for the Hickman arm was £1803.
4. The 95% confidence interval for the mean cost per patient for the Hickman arm was between £462 and £3215.
5. The quality-adjusted life years for the Hickman arm was similar to the TIVAS arm.
6. The quality-adjusted life years for the Hickman arm was -0.01.
7. The 95% confidence interval for the quality-adjusted life years for the Hickman arm was between -0.15 and 0.15.

messages.content:
Statement: The economic evaluation showed that Hickman arm was associated with greater mean cost per patient £1803 (95% CI 462, 3215), but similar quality-adjusted life years −0.01 (95% CI −0.15, 0.15) than the TIVAS arm.
